<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-11-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-11-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="905" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d905">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Jay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-11-04"><hi rend="italic">November 4,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 718.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of Mr.
                            Leishman’s No. 912, of the 13th ultimo, in further relation to the
                            proposed new stamp law.</p>
                        <p>Mr. Leishman’s course in protesting to the Turkish Government against the
                            imposition of such a tax upon American citizens in Turkey is
                            approved.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">F. B. Loomis</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>